1. To check the whether git is installed, run the command-- ls -la 
2. To install the git pacakage run-- git init (If you run this command the git pacakage is installed in that specific directory only)
3. Pulling files from Git and step by step to update the git file 
Example:
--> git pull https://github.com/kunaram/test 
--> vi Firstfile1.txt
--> git add Firstfile1.txt [we can also use git add * but it will make  effect of current directory to Git Hub]
--> git commit Firstfile1.txt
--> git commit -m "updated the text file" [Desired to show as a message in Git]
--> git push Firstfile1.txt 
--> git push https://github.com/kunaram/test  
